HEADWORD: Transprose
<hw>Trans*prose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>trans-</ets> + <ets>prose</ets>.]</ety> <def>To change from prose
into verse; to versify; also, to change from verse into prose.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

